Cassandra-Client

This module aids developers in connecting to Cassandra via the familiar
DBI interfaces. The current implementation is incomplete, though later
releases will hopefully implement the full CQL3 language.

This module is entirely written in Perl.


INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Cassandra::Client

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Cassandra-Client

    AnnoCPAN, Annotated CPAN documentation
        http://annocpan.org/dist/Cassandra-Client

    CPAN Ratings
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/Cassandra-Client

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Cassandra-Client/


